{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"96939015-53a4-4b35-a2c8-8b2d5274a4c7","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n**No, you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`.** That property was the interim opt-in for .NET 9 SDK. In .NET 10, native MTP support in `dotnet test` is controlled by a new property:\n\n```xml\n<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n```\n\nI've replaced the old property in your `TestProject.csproj`. The rest of your setup (`EnableMSTestRunner`, `OutputType=Exe`, MSTest 3.8) is already correct for MTP.\n\n**What changed:** .NET 10 ships a rebuilt `dotnet test` that talks directly to MTP test hosts (no VSTest bridge). `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform` is the single flag to enable it. The old `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is ignored/deprecated.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"45bf4641-4a5a-4386-b385-f98f9a11e47f","outputTokens":222},"id":"c380797f-9693-4bfa-af96-9c8a2248767f","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:47:30.327Z","parentId":"9ec69222-856b-4b48-8609-6f7221227661"}
